06:30.724 --> 06:33.100
Walk the fuck out.

06:36.396 --> 06:38.939
My marriage is dead, Ron.

06:39.149 --> 06:41.233
[SOBBING]
I'm all alone all the time.

06:41.443 --> 06:43.736
- Even when I'm not.
- So am I.

06:43.945 --> 06:46.739
- Oh, Ron.
- Min... Mindy!

06:46.948 --> 06:50.659
I don't wanna be stuck.
I don't wanna be alone anymore.

06:50.869 --> 06:52.453
- Min.
- Oh, Ron.

06:52.662 --> 06:56.624
I just... I've always felt that there's
something between you and me.

06:56.833 --> 06:59.126
- Oh, Min...
- This just feels so easy and so right.

06:59.336 --> 07:00.920
- Doesn't it?
- Mindy.

07:01.129 --> 07:04.965
Oh, Ron.
Ron, I wouldn't have left you on that stage.

07:05.175 --> 07:09.136
I wouldn't have left you standing
at that podium.

07:09.346 --> 07:12.765
I would not have left you
alone on that stage.

07:13.016 --> 07:15.684
Mindy, he's... He's paying!
He's signing his credit card!

07:15.894 --> 07:17.394
MINDY: Hurry. Hurry. Hurry.
RONNIE: Ah.

07:17.604 --> 07:18.938
[GRUNTING]

07:19.147 --> 07:21.816
- Oh. Come on.
- He's exiting. He's exiting!

07:22.317 --> 07:23.901
MINDY: Oh, hurry.
- He's coming!

07:24.111 --> 07:25.486
MINDY:
Okay.

07:34.454 --> 07:36.163
- Twix bar.
- Thanks.

07:36.373 --> 07:38.249
Don't mention it.

07:44.172 --> 07:45.464
[KNOCKS]

07:47.175 --> 07:49.677
LENORE: No, I don't think you
understand me clearly.

07:49.886 --> 07:51.679
Where am I even calling?
Is this India?

07:51.888 --> 07:54.682
Can I speak to your manager, please?

07:54.891 --> 07:59.311
Listen, I know your name is not
John Smith. It's Abdul or Sharif or Malik.

07:59.521 --> 08:03.357
And you're in some call center in India.
So stop pretending your name is John...

08:03.567 --> 08:05.860
...and you're in Michigan
and get me your manager.

08:06.069 --> 08:08.737
Here. That's a thousand dollars.
I gotta get to work.

08:08.947 --> 08:10.614
A thousand? You're short.

08:10.824 --> 08:14.118
A thousand's all I have, okay?
You wanna see my bank statement?

08:15.120 --> 08:19.206
I need 500 more. This is not a suggestion,
Ray. It's not pay-what-you-can.

08:19.416 --> 08:21.709
Why don't you keep that
as a parting gift?

08:21.918 --> 08:24.295
Oh, I'm sorry. Are you going somewhere?

08:24.504 --> 08:28.048
Look, I... I need to...

08:28.550 --> 08:30.259
...take a break.

08:30.468 --> 08:32.553
A break from what?

08:35.015 --> 08:38.142
- From this business.
- Why, did your dick break?

08:38.351 --> 08:40.644
I need to make some changes in my life.

08:40.854 --> 08:43.314
Oh, okay.

08:44.316 --> 08:47.151
Go ahead and quit. Go back to your tent.

08:47.360 --> 08:50.029
Go back to being a nobody
with your nobody friend Tanya.

08:50.238 --> 08:52.156
- Leave Tanya out of it.
- Fuck Tanya.

08:52.324 --> 08:55.075
She owes me a lot more than money.
I've got Liz booked this afternoon.

08:55.243 --> 08:57.953
Are you gonna see her or not?

09:03.126 --> 09:05.878
What is going on, Ray?
What is this about?

09:06.087 --> 09:09.256
- It's none of your business.
- Is this about Jessica?

09:11.009 --> 09:13.719
What, you think you're gonna
get back together with her?

09:13.929 --> 09:15.721
She left you for a reason, Ray.

09:15.931 --> 09:17.765
Maybe there's a reason
she wants me back.

09:17.974 --> 09:21.268
Why? You think you've changed
and she's gonna come back to you?

09:22.229 --> 09:25.189
I don't need this. And I don't need you.

09:25.398 --> 09:28.108
And I am not a nobody. I'm a father.

09:28.318 --> 09:30.152
I'm a coach. I'm a teacher.

09:30.362 --> 09:32.696
And I used to be a pretty good husband.

09:32.906 --> 09:36.951
And if I get another shot at it,
I'm not gonna screw it up this time.

09:49.965 --> 09:52.549
Hey, uh, Koontz.

09:52.759 --> 09:54.760
Turn that off, will you?

09:54.970 --> 09:56.095
Hey, how are you?

09:56.304 --> 09:58.681
How's things? How are the, uh...?

10:00.267 --> 10:01.350
How's the, uh...?

10:02.560 --> 10:06.105
- I'm okay, Ray. I'm keeping busy.
- Good. Yeah, busy's good.

10:06.314 --> 10:07.606
- Yeah.
- So...

10:07.816 --> 10:10.401
...still interested in making me
an offer on the...

10:11.111 --> 10:12.861
You wanna sell me your house?

10:13.363 --> 10:14.863
Yeah. Uh...

10:15.991 --> 10:19.493
Well, I don't know, Ray. I'm not sure.

10:23.248 --> 10:27.918
Well, uh, you said you were
a couple months ago.

10:28.878 --> 10:30.713
Thought I'd come to you first.

10:30.922 --> 10:33.090
Better check with my wife.

10:44.728 --> 10:46.687
TANYA:
Frances!

10:53.528 --> 10:55.362
Please, Frances.

10:55.947 --> 10:58.240
- Don't be frightened.
- Go away.

10:58.450 --> 10:59.992
You're gonna have to run me over.

11:00.201 --> 11:03.746
- I'm gonna call the police.
- Frances, I'm just here to apologize.

11:03.955 --> 11:06.248
I don't care why you're here.
I'm going to church.

11:06.458 --> 11:08.959
Frances, please, just give me
30 seconds to apologize.

11:09.169 --> 11:11.003
- May I approach your window, please?
- No.

11:11.212 --> 11:12.713
- I'm asking permission.
- No.

11:12.922 --> 11:16.592
I'm not here to scare or intimidate you or
make you feel like you're being blackmailed.

11:16.801 --> 11:18.177
I don't care why you're here.

11:18.386 --> 11:20.554
I was wrong, all right? I'm guilty.

11:20.764 --> 11:24.600
I'm gonna pay back every penny. When you
go to church, I hope you will pray for me.

11:24.809 --> 11:27.436
But for right now, please,
just for a moment...

11:27.645 --> 11:30.856
...may I approach your window
just for a moment, please?

11:32.484 --> 11:34.610
Look, I know. I know I've been a bully.

11:34.819 --> 11:37.154
I have given you every
reason not to like me...

11:37.364 --> 11:39.573
...but I'm not here to talk about me.

11:39.783 --> 11:42.242
I'm here to talk about you and Mike.

11:42.452 --> 11:45.913
Whenever I think of Mike, I think of you.

11:46.706 --> 11:49.166
- I'm sorry.
- When you're my age...

11:49.376 --> 11:54.296
...and you meet someone
and it turns out only to be a mirage...

11:54.506 --> 11:57.091
Mike is not a mirage.

11:57.300 --> 12:00.010
He's a nice man who...
He likes you so much.

12:00.220 --> 12:04.223
- He would never do anything to hurt you.
- You don't understand.

12:04.432 --> 12:06.975
I know I was paying for him.

12:08.019 --> 12:11.814
Someday, he'll look at me
and he'll remember.

12:12.357 --> 12:14.775
I mean, what kind of woman...

12:16.277 --> 12:19.947
...is willing to pay for sex?

12:20.156 --> 12:23.117
What basis is that for a relationship?

12:23.326 --> 12:26.328
Frances, you just have to believe.

12:26.538 --> 12:30.416
This man, he loves you.
Just believe that.

12:30.625 --> 12:35.295
Frances, you and him,
it's whatever you want it to be.

12:49.394 --> 12:50.936
Jess.

12:53.148 --> 12:55.149
After the awards...

12:55.442 --> 12:57.901
...Mindy tried to jerk me off.

12:58.653 --> 13:01.113
She tried, I stopped her.

13:01.322 --> 13:06.952
I took her hand
and I pulled it out of my pants.

13:08.538 --> 13:13.292
- What?
- I said, "Mindy, I need you to stop."

13:13.501 --> 13:16.628
Mindy gave you a hand job?

13:16.838 --> 13:20.841
That's not the point. The point is
you went to see another dermatologist...

13:21.050 --> 13:23.135
...Mindy touched me...

13:24.679 --> 13:26.430
...they cancel each other out.

13:26.639 --> 13:29.057
We're even-steven, right?

13:29.476 --> 13:30.893
No.

13:34.689 --> 13:37.691
I need a break, Ron.

13:37.901 --> 13:42.070
Me and the kids, my mom,
we need to get away for a little while.

13:43.364 --> 13:45.532
You know, I shouldn't have told you
about the hand job.

13:45.700 --> 13:47.201
[SCOFFS]

13:47.660 --> 13:50.078
It's not about the hand job, Ron.

13:51.122 --> 13:53.332
Is that it?

13:53.750 --> 13:55.375
Is that what happens?

13:55.585 --> 13:59.421
I give you everything I have,
and you leave?

13:59.631 --> 14:01.840
I can't live with you anymore.

14:02.509 --> 14:04.051
Jess...

14:04.469 --> 14:06.595
...I forgive you.

14:07.096 --> 14:10.015
If that's what you need,
I will sleep on the couch...

14:10.225 --> 14:12.309
...I'll sleep in the garage.

14:12.519 --> 14:16.271
- I just need you to think about it.
- I've thought about it a lot.

14:18.566 --> 14:20.901
I've thought about it a lot.

14:24.906 --> 14:25.948
[LAUGHING AND CHATTERING]

14:26.115 --> 14:28.283
RAY:
The players got that look.

14:28.493 --> 14:30.160
The playoffs.

14:30.370 --> 14:31.995
What the season's been about.

14:33.289 --> 14:34.957
Now it's here.

14:38.962 --> 14:40.921
They didn't make it by themselves, Mike.

14:41.422 --> 14:43.465
Our guys got there
because you and me...

14:45.093 --> 14:47.970
...well, we care a little bit more
than the rest of them.

14:49.472 --> 14:52.099
We got Hunter, round one.

14:52.308 --> 14:54.142
That's a tough team.
What do you think?

14:55.228 --> 14:59.022
Ray, I'm sitting here
because this is still my desk.

14:59.232 --> 15:01.942
And right now it's...

15:02.777 --> 15:04.820
...the best place for me to go.

15:05.947 --> 15:07.531
Okay.

15:11.160 --> 15:13.412
Third baseman's
the only real bat they've got.

15:13.621 --> 15:16.039
We pitch around him, we'll be fine.

15:16.332 --> 15:17.666
What else you got for me?

15:24.841 --> 15:27.509
Mike, I fucked up.
I had no idea what was going on.

15:27.719 --> 15:29.678
But I do know...

15:31.014 --> 15:32.055
[SIGHS]

15:32.223 --> 15:34.600
...you were happy.

15:34.809 --> 15:37.060
You shouldn't let that slip away.

15:57.206 --> 15:58.874
RAY:
Hey.

15:59.792 --> 16:02.669
- Thanks for coming, Jess.
- What are you doing, Ray?

16:02.879 --> 16:04.588
RAY:
Ah, you were right.

16:04.797 --> 16:07.716
I grew up here. So what?

16:07.925 --> 16:11.178
- What?
- I'm selling the house.

16:12.221 --> 16:13.680
Ray, you love this house.

16:13.890 --> 16:15.891
I know, but I'm gonna
get another house.

16:16.100 --> 16:19.770
A bigger one, a better one.
It might not be by the lake, but...

16:19.979 --> 16:22.022
Ray, I have to tell you something.

16:22.231 --> 16:24.608
I have to tell you something too.

16:25.109 --> 16:28.528
Last night in the lake, in the tent...

16:29.572 --> 16:31.281
...I don't want that to stop.

16:31.491 --> 16:33.617
And I don't want you to go away.

16:34.118 --> 16:36.995
I don't want you to forget about it...

16:37.205 --> 16:39.831
...or pretend it never happened.

16:40.041 --> 16:42.000
I don't know what I'm doing...

16:42.210 --> 16:45.712
...but I do know I was happiest with you,
so I'm asking:

16:46.255 --> 16:48.090
What do I do?

16:49.050 --> 16:51.218
Tell me what to do to get you back.

16:54.639 --> 16:57.516
- Just say it and I'll do it.
- It's not about that.

16:58.393 --> 16:59.518
[SIGHS]

16:59.686 --> 17:02.979
I was with you for 20 years. I...

17:03.231 --> 17:04.856
I love you.

17:05.608 --> 17:07.901
I know you, but...

17:09.987 --> 17:12.906
I can't be with you right now.
I can't just go from man to man.

17:13.116 --> 17:16.618
I have to be on my own
for a little while.

17:23.126 --> 17:25.377
Say okay, Ray.

17:26.963 --> 17:29.089
Say good luck.

17:30.466 --> 17:32.050
Say you're proud of me.

17:33.219 --> 17:34.970
Did Lenore talk to you?

17:35.138 --> 17:37.931
Uh, I have to go.

17:52.905 --> 17:54.239
Mom?

17:58.327 --> 18:00.495
Wow. New office.

18:02.623 --> 18:04.708
It's big.

18:04.917 --> 18:07.252
You got The Seventh Seal framed.

18:07.462 --> 18:09.629
What do you care?
It went right over your head.

18:09.839 --> 18:12.924
Mom, I was 10. You took me
to see The Seventh Seal when I was 10.

18:13.134 --> 18:16.553
Some parents never take their children
anywhere. What do you want, Tanya?

18:16.763 --> 18:20.182
Uh, Mom, I'm sorry,
I need to ask you a favor.

18:20.391 --> 18:22.809
Just will you hear me out
before you say no?

18:24.145 --> 18:25.395
[TANYA SIGHS]

18:26.647 --> 18:28.482
I need to get the necklace back.

18:28.691 --> 18:34.780
The gift? And, um, I need to get
the money back from Marvin too.

18:34.989 --> 18:38.283
He... He offered to pay. Do you remember?

18:40.369 --> 18:43.038
You wanna be reimbursed
for my dinner?

18:43.247 --> 18:49.753
Mom, I know. I'm sorry.
Look, you were right. I can't afford it.

18:50.755 --> 18:55.675
But, uh, please, I need the money.

19:02.225 --> 19:03.725
[VERA-JOAN CLEARS THROAT]

20:25.099 --> 20:27.475
Howard, it's, uh...

20:28.477 --> 20:30.979
...a little low.
- It's cash, Ray.

20:32.064 --> 20:33.815
My house is worth twice this.

20:34.025 --> 20:36.860
Nobody can get a loan these days, Ray.
Everything's crashing.

20:37.570 --> 20:41.114
We save on broker fees.
I'll write you a check.

20:41.782 --> 20:43.366
What do you say?

20:47.622 --> 20:49.205
I'll get back to you.

20:51.083 --> 20:52.500
DAMON:
You can't sell the house, Dad.

20:52.710 --> 20:55.921
- I'll get another one.
- Yeah, but we like this house.

20:56.130 --> 20:57.881
You'll have your own rooms.

20:58.090 --> 21:01.259
Why can't you just finish fixing this one,
like you promised?

21:01.469 --> 21:03.970
- We're like orphans.
- You're not orphans, guys.

21:04.180 --> 21:06.681
Orphans don't have parents.
You have two great parents.

21:06.891 --> 21:10.352
- Then we're homeless.
- Homeless orphans. This sucks.

21:10.561 --> 21:13.813
You're not homeless. I have a home
and I'll have another home soon.

21:14.023 --> 21:18.735
Yeah, but right now we're living in a hotel
and we left all of our stuff at Ronnie's.

21:18.945 --> 21:22.405
He's probably, like, in my room right now
touching all my stuff.

21:22.573 --> 21:24.950
- Sniffing it.
- Guys, knock it off, will you?

21:25.159 --> 21:29.537
Your mother needs her space right now
and you need to support that.

21:29.747 --> 21:33.249
She needs space from that weirdo Lenore.
I mean, why is she always around?

21:33.459 --> 21:37.462
Well, she's not around right now.
Right now it's just the three of us, right?

21:37.672 --> 21:40.298
And, uh, we've got hamburgers
and hot dogs.

21:40.508 --> 21:41.800
Okay? Who's hungry?

21:42.009 --> 21:44.219
Dad, did you invite Tanya?

21:46.931 --> 21:49.099
- Hi.
DAMON: Hey.

21:49.308 --> 21:51.059
We're having a barbecue.

21:51.268 --> 21:54.646
Yeah, great. Ahem. It smells great.

21:54.814 --> 21:57.941
Um, can I talk to you for a second?

21:58.818 --> 22:01.653
Take over, will you? I'll be right back.

22:07.118 --> 22:09.536
So I... I got the money, Ray.

22:09.745 --> 22:13.415
I got it all back
and I'm giving it to Frances.

22:16.502 --> 22:19.921
- That's not good enough.
- No, I know.

22:20.131 --> 22:21.715
I know.

22:22.341 --> 22:25.260
- I trusted you.
- Look, I fucked up, okay?

22:25.469 --> 22:27.679
I fucked up. I don't know, I just, uh...

22:27.888 --> 22:33.351
I didn't do any of it to hurt you or Mike
or Frances or anyone. I just got off track.

22:33.561 --> 22:37.439
I don't... I don't...
I don't even know what happened.

22:41.736 --> 22:45.447
[SOBBING] Look, I just...
I need you to forgive me, okay?

22:51.370 --> 22:54.122
That is so fucked up.

22:56.375 --> 22:59.169
Come here. Come on.

23:00.046 --> 23:02.547
What, are you gonna
drown me in the lake?

23:02.757 --> 23:05.759
I'd understand if you did.

23:05.968 --> 23:08.053
Or if you wanted to.

23:09.096 --> 23:11.848
RAY: I don't.
- Where are we going?

23:12.016 --> 23:13.516
RAY:
Shh.

23:13.934 --> 23:16.811
This is my favorite place in the world.

23:28.074 --> 23:30.283
So, uh... So that's it?

23:30.493 --> 23:34.204
You're gonna be
with Lenore now for good?

23:34.413 --> 23:36.164
I don't know.

23:37.333 --> 23:39.334
I told her I quit.

23:39.877 --> 23:41.628
- You did?
- Yeah.

23:41.837 --> 23:43.171
How did that go over?

23:43.380 --> 23:45.548
Ah, you know, it's Lenore.
How do you think?

23:46.842 --> 23:49.052
Ah, you know.

23:49.261 --> 23:53.765
I think I'm still in love
with my ex-wife.

23:54.391 --> 23:59.187
But I got no money,
she's best friends with Lenore...

23:59.396 --> 24:03.566
- How am I supposed to get her back?
- Maybe I could help.

24:04.610 --> 24:07.070
- You wanna help me get my wife back?
- I could try.

24:07.279 --> 24:09.948
I know a lot about women.

24:10.574 --> 24:13.576
Yeah, okay, Tanya.

24:18.707 --> 24:22.293
Come on, Ray,
we've made women happy, right?

24:22.461 --> 24:25.630
With Happiness Consultants.

24:26.173 --> 24:29.217
Until we forgot the happiness part.

24:30.803 --> 24:32.470
You think?

24:33.764 --> 24:36.641
We could do it again, if you wanted.

24:43.566 --> 24:46.192
Can I stay for the barbecue?

24:48.195 --> 24:49.946
Okay.

25:04.336 --> 25:06.629
RAY:
I remember the day we moved in.

25:06.839 --> 25:09.215
I was 6 years old.

25:09.717 --> 25:12.635
I thought it was
the greatest house I'd ever seen...

25:12.845 --> 25:15.972
...and I was the luckiest kid in Detroit.

25:17.641 --> 25:20.351
It was time to get lucky again.
